          "metadataSource": "official-anvio-help-index-and-page",
          "documentation": "# anvi-setup-pfams\n\nDownload and setup Pfam data from the EBI.\n\n🔙 To the main page of anvi’o programs and artifacts.\n\n## Authors\n\n## Can consume\n\nThis program seems to know what its doing. It needs no input material from its user. Good program.\n\n## Can provide\n\npfams-data \n\n## Usage\n\nThis program downloads and organizes a local copy of the data from EBI’s Pfam database for use in function annotation. This program generates a pfams-data artifact, which is required to run the program anvi-run-pfams .\n\n### Set up Pfams data\n\n```\n\nanvi-setup-pfams\n\nBy default, this data is stored at `anvio/data/misc/Pfam`. To set up this data in a non-default location, run\n\n```\n\nanvi-setup-pfams --pfam-data-dir path/to/location\n\nIf you already have a pfams-data artifact and are trying to redownload this data, run\n\n```\n\nanvi-setup-pfams --reset\n\nEdit this file to update this information.\n\n## Additional Resources\n\nAre you aware of resources that may help users better understand the utility of this program? Please feel free to edit this file on GitHub. If you are not sure how to do that, find the `__resources__` tag in this file to see an example."
