          "metadataSource": "official-anvio-help-index",
          "documentation": "# pdb-db\n\nA DB-type anvi’o artifact. This artifact is typically generated, used, and/or exported by anvi’o (and not provided by the user)..\n\n🔙 To the main page of anvi’o programs and artifacts.\n\n## Provided by\n\nanvi-setup-pdb-database \n\n## Required or used by\n\nanvi-gen-structure-database \n\n## Description\n\n## What is this thing?\n\nThis is a comprehensive database of protein structures downloaded from the PDB RSCB that are non-redundant. Currently, it is used for those who want to run anvi-gen-structure-database without an internet connection.\n\n## Where does it come from?\n\nA pdb-db can be created via the program anvi-setup-pdb-database . Alternatively, a pdb-db that contains custom structures not found in the RCSB PDB can in theory be generated by the user, but anvi’o currently offers no reasonable way of doing this.\n\n## Notes\n\nThe pdb-db generated via anvi-setup-pdb-database is ~20GB.\n\nEdit this file to update this information."
