          "artifactType": "TXT",
          "description": "A fixation index matrix is what it sounds like (a matrix of fixation indices) and is generated by anvi-gen-fixation-index-matrix . This is a distance matrix where each column represents a metagenome/sample and each row represents a metagenome/sample, so each cell represents the fixation index between two samples. The fixation index is a number from 0 (maximum similarity) to 1 (maximum distance).",
