          "metadataSource": "official-anvio-help-index",
          "documentation": "# interacdome-data\n\nA DATA-type anvi’o artifact. This artifact is typically generated, used, and/or exported by anvi’o (and not provided by the user)..\n\n🔙 To the main page of anvi’o programs and artifacts.\n\n## Provided by\n\nanvi-setup-interacdome \n\n## Required or used by\n\nanvi-run-interacdome \n\n## Description\n\nThis artifact stores the data downloaded by anvi-setup-interacdome and is required to run anvi-run-interacdome .\n\nAs described in the InteracDome blogpost , this data includes the tab-separated files from InteracDome and the Pfam 31.0 HMMs for the subset of Pfams found in the InteracDome dataset.\n\nBy default, this data is stored in `anvio/data/misc/InteracDome`, but a custom path can be set when the user runs anvi-setup-interacdome if desired.\n\nEdit this file to update this information."
