          "description": "A script that takes a FASTQ file that is not paired-end (i.e., R1 alone) and converts it into two FASTQ files that are paired-end (i.e., R1 and R2). This is a quick-and-dirty workaround that halves each read from the original FASTQ and puts one half in the FASTQ file for R1 and puts the reverse-complement of the second half in the FASTQ file for R2. If you've ended up here, things have clearly not gone very well for you, and Evan, who battled similar battles and ended up implementing this solution wholeheartedly sympathizes",
